HEADWORD: tabasheer
<hw>tab`a*sheer"</hw> <pr>(t⟦acr⟧b`⟦adot⟧*sh⟦emac⟧r")</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per. <ets>tab⟦amac⟧sh⟦imac⟧r</ets>: cf. Skr.
<ets>tvakksh⟦imac⟧r⟦amac⟧</ets>, <ets>tvaksh⟦imac⟧r⟦amac⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A concretion in the joints of the bamboo, which consists largely or
chiefly of pure silica. It is highly valued in the East Indies as a
medicine for the cure of bilious vomitings, bloody flux, piles, and
various other diseases.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tabbinet</ent>⟦br⟧
